## 🔵 Architecture — Long-Term

[x] 19. Unified CPU/GPU reduction pipeline via pic.reduce
        - Define link/annihilate/dup/erase/fire_op in scf+arith+memref dialect
        - Lower once to LLVM for CPU; once to gpu+spirv for GPU
        - Target: CPU (std LLVM), general GPU (Vulkan/SPIR-V), shader GPU (perf)

[ ] 20. 128-bit node layout audit + PICR history extension 🔴
        # Classic audit (was item 20) now merged with PICR layout requirement.
        # Prerequisite for A5–A8, items 21, R6.
        - Current: int32_t[4] per node — correct size per spec ✅
        - Verify: polarity encoded in port value (atomic bit-field), not separate field
        - Lock-free redex detection via single atomic CAS on principal port
        # PICR extension:
        - Add a second 128-bit word allocated only for nodes inside boundary regions:
            [ log_ptr:32 | flags:8 | reserved:24 ]
          log_ptr: history-chain pointer (null for nodes outside boundaries)
          flags: bit 0 = inside_boundary, bit 1 = log_active, bit 2 = reverse_eligible
        - Outside boundaries: second word omitted; hot path stays at 128 bits (classic width)
        - Update alloc_node in PicRuntimeDialect.td to accept a boundary_ctx argument
          so the allocator knows whether to provision the second word

[ ] 20b. δ reverse synchronization barrier 🟡
        # Part of the 128-bit layout audit. Prerequisite: item 20, A7.
        - Duplication in reverse requires both backward signals to arrive before merge fires
        - Per-δ-node atomic arrival counter (i8) stored in the flags field (item 20)
        - Worker thread: on R ⋈ δ, atomically decrement counter; fire inverse rule only
          when counter reaches 0 (both aux backward signals have arrived)
        - Prevents partial merges from corrupting the graph during concurrent reverse passes
        - Add to A2 rule table: δ reverse entry pointing to barrier-gated merge handler

[ ] 21. E-graph congruence (Rule 4) + origins attribute 🟡
        # Prerequisite: A4 (done). PICR requires origins attr for correct reverse splitting.
        - Inside boundaries: hash normal forms, merge identical subgraphs
        - Fires continuously during reduction (not a post-pass)
        - GPU: congruence hashing as a parallel reduce kernel
        # PICR extension:
        - Each merged node carries an `origins` attribute: the list of wires that were
          redirected to it during congruence merging
        - On reverse pass: merged node splits back along its origins wires when different
          backward signals demand it — origins attr provides the routing table for split

